The paper proposes a novel approach for EEG classification using graph-based techniques and machine learning. The paper focuses on improving the classification performance by selecting EEG time series based on their similarity and discriminative power. This work involves the use of machine learning algorithms, graph theory, and signal processing techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and signal processing (cs.SI).
